What is Statistical Learning?

  • Suppose we observe a quantitative response \(Y\) and \(p\) dimensional predictors, \(X_1, X_2, \cdots, X_p\).

  • Assume there is some relationship between \(Y\) and \(X=(X_1, X_2, \cdots, X_p)\) which can be expressed in a general form as:

\[Y=f(X)+\epsilon \tag{1}.\]

  • \(\color{#ff8531}\text{ What is }f?\)

  • \(\color{#ff8531}\text{ What is }\epsilon?\)

  • \(\color{#ff8531}\text{What is Statistical learning}?\)
